data.responseFromOwnerText:
Thanks for your review Mel-lisa, sorry to hear that you were disappointed, it's certainly not the standard we provide to people on a daily basis.
The croquettes are described on the menu as 'Cheese & N'Duja Croquettes' so I'm surprised and unsure how that miscommunication has happened. 
I hope you return soon so we can provide you with our usual great service.

data.text: First of all, I have to acknowledge that the food is always nice here and if that’s all you care about, then  you’ll likely enjoy yourself. However, the standard of service is largely poor and you can often find long delays. Still, we have been happy to go back for the nice food. Unfortunately our most recent visit was completely spoiled when a waiter dropped a place full of food on my partner. A brief apology followed and an offer to get a cloth to help clear up…then another delay before a useless clump of damp paper towels arrived because they didn’t have a cloth (!?). My partner was sat with a spoiled top and we quickly asked for the bill (no gesture of good will as an apology or apology from the manager). To top it off, my partner had asked for a Sauvignon blanc and we’d been charged for the most expensive one too. We probably won’t be back which is a real shame.

data.text:
Decor is modern and relaxed, lots of seating options - at the bar, in a booth, table in the window & bar stools with high tables so you can find somewhere suitable for just a drink, nibbles or full blown meal.
We decided to have a blow out as we were starving! Both Pescatorians we were attracted by the many vegetarian/vegan options compared to other places.
Stand out dish was the bang bang cauliflower with amazing Asian dressing. Creamy garlic mushrooms were very satisfying.
We ordered 4 of the tapas dishes each plus a side each. I would recommend only three each max as we we're stuffed by the end.
As others have said prices are reasonable as they use very fresh good quality ingredients.
Staff we're helpful and friendly when we were asking about the different dishes.
We would definitely return but order less! 😂

data.text:
Fantastic food
- I had the steak sandwich which was perfectly seasoned and the chips that come with it were some of the best ive ever had, Actual home made cut chips! strongly suggest to anybody looking for light lunch.
Really nice decor inside too and pleasant staff.
data.name: Abdul Kashem

data.text: Very vague menu, so if you wish eat a full meal avoid
data.name: richard rostron
data.responseFromOwnerText: Hi Richard, we are extremely proud of our small plates menu and sorry it didn't appeal to you - it's not vague in the slightest - we advertise loud and clear what we are and what we do - it's a shame you've rated us on something you didn't eat? We'd be delighted to host you again if you were willing to try.

data.text:
Food gets it a star, service was abysmal. About an hour to get breakfast, or should I say lunch, with no apology when I went to complain.Then food delivered to the table at different times, all in all, shocking...

Invited back and everything spot on. Food was great again but good service, lovely chat with Martin (the owner) and not a thing out of place. We'll be back again soon.
data.name: Rick Ashworth
data.responseFromOwnerText: Hi Rick, I appreciate your feedback and as you can see from other reviews this is not Suburban Green’s usual standard. I understood from my team working on Sunday that your long wait was acknowledged and apologised for and that there was some recompense, if this was not the case then I need to understand how this breakdown in communication has occurred. I would really appreciate if you are local, to arrange a  coffee at your convenience, or alternatively please call me at the restaurant 01625525588 so we can discuss in more detail and I can resolve the service issues. Kind regards Martin Lowe (Owner)

data.text: Excellent place for an excellent G&T!!

data.text: Great light plates with its of flavour. Pleasant modern decor. Staff are nice but service is very slow from the kitchen and it wasn't even busy.
